<head>Sacred Stories 04: Wisahketchahk Preaches to the Wolves</head>
<docauthor>Coming-Day</docauthor>

<p n="1">

<seg n="1.1">
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
<w canon="mistahi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="greatly" stem="mistahi">mistahi</w>
<w canon="kitimâkisiw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="be_pitiable" stem="kitimâkisi" suffix="-w">kitimâkisiw</w>
;
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="wiya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="WIYA" stem="wiya">wya</w>
<w canon="kîkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPRq" sgloss="what" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
<w canon="otayôwinis" class="ni" gcat="0sNIof3s" prefix="3" sgloss="clothes" stem="ayiwinis" suffix="0">otayôwinis</w>
<w canon="ê-wîkicik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="live_there" stem="wîki" suffix="-cik">ê-wîkicik</w>
,
<w canon="ê-ayâcik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="have" stem="ayâ" suffix="-cik">êh-ayâcik</w>
.
<gloss>Wisahketchahk was very poor; he had not even clothing in his house, where he dwelt with his family.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.2">
<w canon="kîtahtawê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="at_times" stem="kêtahtawê">kîtahtawê</w>
<w canon="takosinwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="arrive" stem="takosin" suffix="-wak">takosinwak</w>
<w canon="wêmistikôsiwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="French_person" stem="wêmistikôsiw" suffix="-ak">wêmistikôsiwak</w>
,
<w canon="ê-papâ-atâwêcik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj papâ|around" sgloss="buy" stem="atâwê" suffix="-cik">êh-papâ-atâwêcik</w>
<w canon="ahtaya" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="pelt" stem="ahtay" suffix="-a">ahtayah</w>
,
<w canon="mahîhkana" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="wolf" stem="mahîhkan" suffix="-a">mahîhkanah</w>
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="mostoswayâna" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="cow_hide" stem="mostoswayân" suffix="-a">mostoswayânah</w>
.
<gloss>Then at one time arrived some Frenchmen who were going about buying furs, wolf-pelts and buffalo-robes.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.3">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="kîkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="something" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
<w canon="ayâw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="have" stem="ayâ" suffix="-w">ayâw</w>
<w canon="atâwâkan" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="fur" stem="atâwâkan" suffix="0">atâwâkan</w>
.
<gloss>But Wisahketchahk had no furs to sell.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.4">
<w canon="kotakak" class="pr" gcat="3pPR" sgloss="other" stem="kotak" suffix="-3p">kotakak</w>
<w canon="ayîsiyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="person" stem="ayisiyiniw" suffix="-ak">ayîsiyiniwak</w>
<w canon="mistahi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="greatly" stem="mistahi">mistahih</w>
<w canon="ayâwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="have" stem="ayâ" suffix="-wak">ayâwak</w>
;
<w canon="atâwêwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="buy" stem="atâwê" suffix="-wak">atâwêwak</w>
<w canon="êkonik" class="pr" gcat="3pPR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako" suffix="-3p">êkonik</w>
<w canon="mistahi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="greatly" stem="mistahi">mistahi</w>
<w canon="ayiwinisa" class="ni" gcat="0pNI" sgloss="clothes" stem="ayiwinis" suffix="-a">ayôwinisah</w>
;
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="kîkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="something" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
.
<gloss>The other people had many; they bought many clothes, but Wisahketchahk none at all.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="2">

<seg n="2.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="ômisi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="ômisi">ômis</w>
<w canon="itêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-êw">îtêw</w>
<w canon="wêmistikôsiwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="French_person" stem="wêmistikôsiw" suffix="-a">wêmistikôsiwah</w>
:
<q rend="PRE 1 POST0">
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="cî" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="[?]" stem="cî">cî</w>
<w canon="nika-kî-masinahikân" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will kî|can" sgloss="write_things" stem="masinahikê" suffix="-n">nika-kî-masinahikân</w>
?</q>
<gloss>Then he spoke to the Frenchman as follows: “Won't you let me have credit?</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="2.2">
<q rend="PRE 0 POST0">
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="kîkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="something" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
<w canon="atâwâkan" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="fur" stem="atâwâkan" suffix="0">atâwâkan</w>
<w canon="nitayân" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" sgloss="have" stem="ayâ" suffix="-n">nitayân</w>
.</q>
<gloss>I haven't any furs.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="2.3">
<q rend="PRE 0 POST1">
<w canon="mâka" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="but" stem="mâka">mâka</w>
<w canon="kiyipa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="quickly" stem="kiyipa">kiyipah</w>
<w canon="mihcêt" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="many" stem="mihcêt">mihcêt</w>
<w canon="nika-ayân" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="be" stem="ayâ" suffix="-n">nik-âyân</w>
<w canon="ka-tipahikêyân" class="vai" gcat="1sAIcnj" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="pay_for_things" stem="tipahikê" suffix="-yân">ka-tipahikêyân</w>
.</q>
<gloss>But in a short time I shall have a good many with which to pay my debt.”</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="2.4">
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkos</w>
<w canon="ômisi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="ômisi">ômis</w>
<w canon="itwêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-w">îtwêw</w>
;
<w canon="wêmistikôsiwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="French_person" stem="wêmistikôsiw" suffix="-a">wêmistikôsiwah</w>
<w canon="itêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-êw">itêw</w>
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">awah</w>
:
<q rend="PRE 1 POST0">
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="kîkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="something" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
<w canon="ka-kî-tipahikâkân" class="vai" gcat="2sAI" preverbs="ka|will kî|can" sgloss="pay_people" stem="tipahikâkê" suffix="-n">ka-kîh-tipahikâkân</w>
.</q>
<gloss>Thus Wisahketchahk spoke to the Frenchman: “You will not need to pay anything.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="2.5">
<q rend="PRE 0 POST1">
<w canon="kîspin" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="if" stem="kîspin">kîspin</w>
<w canon="miyiyani" class="vta" gcat="2s1sTAsubjunc" sgloss="give_to" stem="miy" suffix="-iyani">miyiyinih</w>
,
<w canon="kiyipa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="quickly" stem="kiyipa">kiyipah</w>
<w canon="nika-ayân" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="be" stem="ayâ" suffix="-n">nik-âyân</w>
.</q>
<gloss>If you give me credit, in a short time I shall have them.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="2a">

<seg n="2a.1">
<q>
<w canon="êha" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="yes" stem="êha">ahâg</w>
!</q>
-
<w canon="wêmistikôsiwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="French_person" stem="wêmistikôsiw" suffix="-ak">wêmistikôsiwak</w>
-
<q>
<w canon="kîkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPRq" sgloss="what" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
<w canon="kinitawêyihtên" class="vti" gcat="2sTI" prefix="2" sgloss="want" stem="nitawêyiht" suffix="-ên">kintawêyihtên</w>
,
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
?</q>
<gloss>“Very well,”  the Frenchmen  “What do you want, Wisahketchahk?”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="3">

<seg n="3.1">
<q>
<w canon="wâpowayâna" class="ni" gcat="0pNI" sgloss="blanket" stem="wâpowayân" suffix="-a">wâpowiyânah</w>
<w canon="nîso" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="two" stem="nîso">nîso</w>
,
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mînah</w>
<w canon="mitâs" class="nda" gcat="3sNDAofxs" prefix="x" sgloss="pants" stem="tâs" suffix="0">mitâs</w>
<w canon="nîso" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="two" stem="nîso">nîso</w>
,
<w canon="miskotâkay" class="ndi" gcat="0sNDIofxs" prefix="x" sgloss="coat" stem="skotâkay" suffix="0">miskotâkay</w>
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mîna</w>
<w canon="nîso" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="two" stem="nîso">nîso</w>
,
<w canon="pâskisikan" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="gun" stem="pâskisikan" suffix="0">pâskisikan</w>
.</q>
<gloss>“Two blankets, two pairs of breeches, and two coats, and a gun.”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="4">

<seg n="4.1">
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotah</w>
<w canon="mistahi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="greatly" stem="mistahi">mistahi</w>
<w canon="ayôwinis" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="clothes" stem="ayiwinis" suffix="0">ayôwinis</w>
<w canon="otinam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="take" stem="otin" suffix="-am">otinam</w>
.
<gloss>Then he took a great deal of clothing.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="4.2">
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkosi</w>
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="kîwêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="go_home" stem="kîwê" suffix="-w">kîwêw</w>
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
.
<gloss>Then Wisahketchahk went home.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="4.3">
<w canon="owîkimâkana" class="nda" gcat="3oNDAof3s" prefix="3" sgloss="spouse" stem="wîkimâkan" suffix="-a">owîkimâkanah</w>
<w canon="miyêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="give_to" stem="miy" suffix="-êw">miyêw</w>
<w canon="kahkiyaw" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="every" stem="kahkiyaw">kahkiyaw</w>
.
<gloss>He gave all of it to his wife.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="5">

<seg n="5.1">
<w canon="ômisi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="ômisi">omisiy</w>
<w canon="itik" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-ik">itik</w>
<w canon="owîkimâkana" class="nda" gcat="3oNDAof3s" prefix="3" sgloss="spouse" stem="wîkimâkan" suffix="-a">owîkimâkanah</w>
:
<q>
<w canon="môhco-kisêyiniw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" prenouns="môhco|crazy" sgloss="old_man" stem="kisêyiniw" suffix="0">mohco-kisêyiniw</w>
,
<w canon="tânita" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="where" stem="tânita">tântah</w>
<w canon="kî-otinaman" class="vti" gcat="2sTIcnj" preverbs="kî|can" sgloss="take" stem="otin" suffix="-aman">ki-ôtinaman</w>
<w canon="ta-tipahikâkêyan" class="vai" gcat="2sAIcnj" preverbs="ta|FUT" sgloss="pay_people" stem="tipahikâkê" suffix="-yan">tah-tipahikâkêyin</w>
?</q>
<gloss>This is what his wife said to him: “Crazy old man, where can you get anything with which to pay?”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="6">

<seg n="6.1">
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkosi</w>
<w canon="itwêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-w">itwêw</w>
,
<q>
<w canon="nôtokêsiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="old_woman" stem="nôtokwêsiw" suffix="0">nôtokêsiw</w>
,
<w canon="pêyakwâw" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="once" stem="pêyakwâw">pêyakwâw</w>
<w canon="nina-nitawâpamâw" class="vta" gcat="1s3sTA" prefix="1" preverbs="dupL|L.REDUP" sgloss="go_to_see" stem="nitawâpam" suffix="-âw">nna-ntawâpamâw</w>
<w canon="wêmistikôsiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="French_person" stem="wêmistikôsiw" suffix="0">wêmistikôsiw</w>
.</q>
<gloss>He answered, “Old woman, once more I shall go see the Frenchmen.”</gloss>
<note>LB's footnote to {nna-ntawâpamâw}:  The combination {nt} does not exist in the full form of Cree words, but is due to the loss of an intermediate short vowel;  See Introduction.  Occasional forms like {na-ntawâpamâw}: “he goes to see him,” are allegro variants for such as {na-nitawâpamâw}; the first syllable here is reduplicative.  This differs from Ojibwa, where {nand-} is probably the normal representation of older {nat-}.</note>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="7">

<seg n="7.1">
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkosi</w>
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="sipwêhtêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="leave" stem="sipwêhtê" suffix="-w">sipwêhtêw</w>
.
<gloss>So he set out.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="8">

<seg n="8.1">
<w canon="ê-pîhtokêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="enter" stem="pîhtikwê" suffix="-t">êh-pîhtokêt</w>
,
<w canon="wêmistikôsiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="French_person" stem="wêmistikôsiw" suffix="0">wêmistikôsiw</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">awah</w>
<w canon="ômisi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="ômisi">omis</w>
<w canon="itêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-êw">îtêw</w>
:
<q>
<w canon="â" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="well" stem="â">âh</w>
,
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
,
<w canon="kipê-tipahikân" class="vai" gcat="2sAI" prefix="2" preverbs="pê|thence" sgloss="pay_for_things" stem="tipahikê" suffix="-n">kipê-tipahikân</w>
?</q>
<gloss>When he entered, the Frenchmen said, “Well, Wisahketchahk, have you come to pay?”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="9">

<seg n="9.1">
<q>
<w canon="namôya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="namôya">namoya</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itwêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-w">itwêw</w>
<w canon="wîsahkêcâhk" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Wisahketchahk" stem="wîsahkêcâhkw" suffix="0">wîsahkêcâhk</w>
;
<q>
<w canon="miyin" class="vta" gcat="2s1sTAimp" sgloss="give_to" stem="miy" suffix="-in">miyin</w>
<w canon="piscipôwin" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="poison" stem="piscipowin" suffix="0">piscipôwin</w>
.</q>
<gloss>“No,” said Wisahketchahk; “Give me some poison.”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="10">

<seg n="10.1">
<q>
<w canon="tânisi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="how" stem="tânisi">tânisi</w>
<w canon="kitôtên" class="vti" gcat="2sTI" prefix="2" sgloss="do_thus" stem="tôt" suffix="-ên">kitôtan</w>
?</q>
<gloss>“What do you want that for?”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="11">

<seg n="11.1">
<q>
<w canon="â" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="ah" stem="â">âh</w>
,
<w canon="mahîhkanak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="wolf" stem="mahîhkan" suffix="-ak">mahîhkanak</w>
<w canon="nika-nipahâwak" class="vta" gcat="1s3pTA" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="kill" stem="nipah" suffix="-âwak">nika-nipahâwak</w>
.</q>
<gloss>“Oh, I am going to kill wolves.”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="12">

<seg n="12.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="miyik" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" sgloss="give_to" stem="miy" suffix="-ik">miyik</w>
<w canon="maskihkiy" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="herb" stem="maskihkiy" suffix="0">maskihkiy</w>
,
<w canon="piscipôwin" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="poison" stem="piscipowin" suffix="0">piscipôwin</w>
.
<gloss>So the other gave him some medicine, poison.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="12.2">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
